title: Sidewall - Fragment, 1850–1900
provenance: Found in the nave of St. John's Church, Cookstown, Ontario. Paper in poor condition. Mounted on muslin.
description: Fragment of irregular outline. All-over pattern of small-scale sprigwork, suggestive of floral sprays.

tombstone.epitaph:
Sidewall - Fragment, 1850–1900.
1850–1900. Machine-printed. Gift of Kenneth E. Kidd. 1947-109-5.
